<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>3300 HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE - Steering Wheel / Clock Spring</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="13">
        <title>Steering Wheel / Clock Spring</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always disconnect power source before working on electrical equipment.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Front and Side Cover</title>
            <figure id="f0901046" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901046.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Steering Wheel Front Cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FRONT COVER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0901047" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901047.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                         scalefitheight="288px"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Releasing Front Cover With Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To release front cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901046">Figure 53, Item 1</hotlnk>), insert removal tool into aperture (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901047">Figure 54</hotlnk>). Phillips head screwdriver may be used.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push tool in to release the locking clips (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901050">Figure 57, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901048" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901048.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Removing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grasp cover as shown (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901048">Figure 55</hotlnk>) and lift cover from steering wheel assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901049" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901049.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Side Cover Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TURN SIGNAL SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SIDE COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RETAINING SCREW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the cover fastener (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901049">Figure 56, Item 3</hotlnk>) openings on the steering wheel covers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert phillips head screwdriver in cover opening, loosen and remove screws retaining
                    covers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove covers.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Locking Clip</title>
            <figure id="f0901050" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901050.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Locking Clip</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOCKING CLIPS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0901051" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Steering Wheel Retaining Nut</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STEERING WHEEL RETAINING NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the retaining nut from the shaft spindle (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901051">Figure 58, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the harness section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901052">Figure 59, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901052" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Steering Wheel Harness Disconnect</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STEERING WHEEL HARNESS CONNECTION</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Steering Wheel</title>
            <figure id="f0901053" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901053.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Mark Shaft and Spindle Alignment</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MARK LOCATION FOR REALIGNMENT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make a corresponding mark on the shaft spindle (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901053">Figure 60, Item 1</hotlnk>) and plate to aid alignment in reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901054" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901054.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                         scalefitheight="288px"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Utilizing Wheel Puller to Remove Steering Wheel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WHEEL PULLER MOUNTED ON STEERING WHEEL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a wheel puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901054">Figure 61, Item 1</hotlnk>) to loosen steering wheel from shaft spindle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove steering wheel from spindle.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Clock Spring</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Follow the installation instructions printed on the clock spring to avoid damage.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0901055" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901055.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Clock Spring</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CLOCK SPRING BODY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CLOCK SPRING HARNESS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPINDLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the clock spring harness (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901056">Figure 63, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the clock spring harness from the dash harness (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901057">Figure 64, Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901056" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901056.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Clock Spring Harness and Attachment Tabs</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CLOCK SPRING ATTACHMENT TABS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CLOCK SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CLOCK SPRING HARNESS CONNECTION</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove Phillips head screws from tabs (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901056">Figure 63, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift clock spring out to remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901057" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901057.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Clock Spring Assembly With Harness</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CLOCK SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CLOCK SPRING HARNESS PIGTAIL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DASH HARNESS CONNECTION</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Door Switch and Flasher Light Modules</title>
            <para>The switch modules in the steering wheel assembly are easily removed. The left hand switch module
                controls the opening and closing of the side passenger entry door. The right side switch module controls
                the amber flasher and red override switch.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0901058" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901058.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Steering Wheel Switch Module Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MODULE DIRECTION FOR REMOVAL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the switch modules from the steering wheel, slide them toward the center of
                    the steering wheel assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
